        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Align refresh menu icon",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Align the custom persistent Refresh menu icon with native AppKit menu action rows.\n- Update the metric regression test for the new icon sizing and alignment values.\n\n## Root Cause\nThe persistent Refresh row uses a custom view so it can stay active while menu tracking is in progress. Its icon metrics used a smaller slot and symbol size than the surrounding native menu items, which made the refresh glyph appear visually offset.\n\n## Impact\nThe Refresh command now lines up with Settings, About, and Quit in the status menu while keeping the persistent refresh row behavior intact.\n\n## Validation\n- `swift test --filter StatusMenuPersistentRefreshTests`\n- `make check`\n- `make test`",
